        {
            "author_info": {
                "name": "Marc Whinery",
                "href": "/profile/Marc-Whinery"
            },
            "answer_text": "The red car. The smaller car. The flashier car. Human nature assigns a higher speed to certain features. That\u2019s one reason why so many people try to beat a train and lose. Smaller things look faster. Without a reason to pick one over the other, the one that catches attention will get his attention. Cops, for all said about them from both sides, are still humans, and run on the same firmware as the rest of us. Even if they try to train some of that out. ",
